The Movement for Democratic Growth headed by Ugenya MP David Ochieng is seeking a coalition deal with NASA.The MDG top brass told the Star they support the opposition and are seeking to formally cement its position in NASA. Article Two of the NASA agreement allows the opposition outfit to enter into agreements with other political parties other than its current affiliate parties. The Article States that the coalition may conclude agreements with other political parties and organisations of like minds and similar objectives. Once concluded, the agreements shall be an integral part of the Coalition Agreement.MDG chairman Titus Ondego said they intend to field candidates in all elective seats other than the presidency.